{
  "texts": [
    "However, one potential limitation of MAE is that it requires the model to reconstruct data in the original space, not in the latent space.",
    "This detail means the model will be required to reconstruct noisy low-level details.",
    "We adapted MAE for HAR, building upon the original implementation [9], which was primarily designed for computer vision tasks.",
    "Our approach involved modifying the iSPL to process inputs as a series of non-overlapping, independent frames, similar to how transformers function.",
    "For the integration to HART, we introduced sensor-specific masking tokens to accommodate the sensor-wise feature of HART."
  ]
}